{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1106: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $p(n)$ denote the partition function of $n$ and let $F(n)$ count the number of distinct prime factors of\\[\\prod_{1\\leq k\\leq n}p(k).\\]Does $F(n)\\to \\infty$ with $n$? Is $F(n)>n$ for all sufficiently large $n$? Current best: Schinzel noted in the Oberwolfach problem book that $F(n)\\to \\infty$ follows from the asymptotic formula for $p(n)$ and a result of Tijdeman \\cite{Ti73}. Ono \\cite{On00} has proved that every prime divides $p(n)$ for some $n\\geq 1$ (indeed this holds, for any fixed prime, for a positive density set of $n$). Prize: no. OEIS: A194259, A194260. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_07e8bc62774b0225","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos1106.erdos_1106.parts.i https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos1106.erdos_1106.parts.i.","id":"vf_b7e80317ef42d011","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/1106.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_07e8bc62774b0225","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1106","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_b7e80317ef42d011","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1106","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_b7e80317ef42d011","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62e